commit.message:
fix: Find rye pythons with and without install directory (#25)

Starting with rye 0.31 (released today), it by default installs python
toolchains without the intermediate install directory (but both options
continue to exist).

As a side effect, this also picks up some other rye toolchains that were
already installed without the intermediate install - for example pypy
toolchains installed with rye.

commit.message:
fix: UTF-8 encoding of shell command output on Windows (#14)

* Fix UTF-8 encoding of shell command output on Windows

On Windows, when running pdm from the command line, it would fail when special characters are in the python path (such as "ä", "ö", "ß").
The fix was implemented as described here: https://stackoverflow.com/a/74607949

* set text=True in subprocess.check_output

verification.payload:
tree c49689b5cf1017df79e4a0d716808e13dc9cb37f
parent 52b9ceed4e465720b83676986a336c6cc572b7f3
author fbeutel <fbeutel@users.noreply.github.com> 1683704685 +0200
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1683704685 +0800

fix: UTF-8 encoding of shell command output on Windows (#14)

On Windows, when running pdm from the command line, it would fail when special characters are in the python path (such as "ä", "ö", "ß").

* set text=True in subprocess.check_output
